son

The
spring
was
a
late
one ;
though
the
beginning
of

May,

on
mountain
heights,
and
it
was

voted
too
cold
for
mountain
expeditions,
so
an
excursion

was
planned
in
Sir
James'
drag,
and
Walter
Forbes
and

his
cousin
happening
to
call
while
the
plan
was
under

discussion,
were
asked
to
join
it,
and
told
to
ask
Mrs.

Seymour
if
she
would
also
do
so.

On
this
day
of
which
we
are
speaking,
Walter
was

riding
to
Scarth
Grange
to
give
her
answer
in
the

affirmative ;
he
said
it
would
be
better
for

to
go

there
than
to
write,
as
he
could
discuss
arrangements

more
fully.
On
arriving
at
the
Grange,
he
was
graciously

received
by
Lady
Scarth.
He
glanced
round
the
room,

and
saw
that
only
Lady
Scarth
was
there.

"
Tell
me
quickly
what
your
mother's
answer
is
?"

she

"
I

most
